release.notes:
One of a set of 12. On some sets, 
Graphics scheme colors for this volume (3) is green-yellow on front and yellow-magenta on rear, not blue-yellow-red.
Text at bottom left of front cover does NOT say "A Jazz Club of America Presentation" but says:
"Produced for the Jazz Club of America, Inc.
by Bill Grauer, Jr. and Orrin Keepnews, Leading Jazz Authorities."

Text on bottom line of rear cover:
"Produced in Cooperation with RCA-VICTOR for J.J. Little and Ives, Inc., N. Y. 19, N. Y."
